        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49136",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "1.9.8 is quite old.  Have you tried using v1.11.11?\r\n\r\nHowever, I do see your point:  If you look the list of allowed CURL options in {{Zend_Http_Client_Adapter_Curl::__construct}} and compare that with the list from the [PHP manual page for {{curl_setopt}}|http:\/\/www.php.net\/manual\/en\/function.curl-setopt.php] there is quite a difference.  ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-11-18T15:22:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-11-18T15:22:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49209",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Apologies...I misread the source of {{Zend_Http_Client_Adapter_Curl}}.  The adapter already passes on all CURL options set via configuration key 'curloptions' or via the setter {{setCurlOption}} just before the call to {{curl_exec}}:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n\/\/ set additional curl options\r\nif (isset($this->_config['curloptions'])) {\r\n    foreach ((array)$this->_config['curloptions'] as $k => $v) {\r\n        if (!in_array($k, $this->_invalidOverwritableCurlOptions)) {\r\n            if (curl_setopt($this->_curl, $k, $v) == false) {\r\n                require_once 'Zend\/Http\/Client\/Exception.php';\r\n                throw new Zend_Http_Client_Exception(sprintf(\"Unknown or erroreous cURL option '%s' set\", $k));\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\nSource: http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/code\/blame.php?repname=Zend+Framework&path=%2Ftrunk%2Flibrary%2FZend%2FHttp%2FClient%2FAdapter%2FCurl.php#l401\r\n\r\ncURL options specified in {{$this->_invalidOverwritableCurlOptions}} cannot be overridden, and are ignored in the code snipped above when encountered.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-12-02T01:49:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-12-02T01:49:06.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
